Kavalla was also one of the four French Post Offices in the Ottoman period that issued  their own stamps between 1893 and 1903: [Cavalle](../cavalle/introduction) (present-day Kavala), Dedeagh (Dedeagatch, present-day Alexandroupoli), Port Lagos, and Vathy (Samos). For these stamps see [Cavelle](../cavelle/introduction).